12.26.23  3:32 am   If all matter in the universe is just particles interacting according to the laws of physics, then there's no real difference between me and this table.

     i'm not following your logic there

      We're just piles of stuff doing exactly what that stuff has to do. Everything I think and feel, even thinking about thinking, is just a bunch of stuff following a list of rules I have no control over.

     i'm not following your logic there either

     The only argument that free will isn't an illusion and that feelings matter, is that they feel like they do,

     i disagree with that

      which feels like circular logic to me.

     yes that argument would feel a bit empty

      I think meaning logically has to come from an external source, but I don't believe in an external source.

     'who' doesnt

      If the universe is a big rube goldberg machine, and we're cogs in it (albeit cogs with an element of randomness thanks to quantum mechanics), how do you derive meaning from it without just saying "I feel like stuff matters so it does"? Because then anything anyone feels is true. The statement "nothing matters" becomes just as true as the statement "everything matters". My brain hurts, my heart hurts, and I just want stuff to matter so badly.

     so then it's safe to say that [whether or not things matter] matters very much to you indeed, if i'm hearing you correctly

     Your music is one of the few things that distracts me and makes me feel better, but you're so wise all the time that I want to hear your thoughts. Not like, telepathically, but you know, on here. 

      in my opinion, if this all-mechanical mindless cause-and-effect 'deterministic' 'no-free-will' thing were true, then we wouldn't be here to perceive it. we wouldn't even be aware of anything. so in my opinion the fact that you are here, aware of your existence, means that there is significant 'wiggle room', 'free choice', 'multiple futures which you can choose between', etc. If this seems bonkers, that's because it is. that's why you're here. if it weren't you'd be somewhere else. your bonkers consciousness has no business in a deterministic system. deterministic systems are already complete and the process of time is not necessary because all the results were already known. If you're looking for evidence of such bonkeristics in science, then you should check out how many different places electrons claim they 'could' be at any given moment
